Label the centre of the spiral with the axial (cube-free) co-ordinates  
(q , r ).  
The six step-vectors of the hexagonal grid are  

E  ( 1 , 0) NE ( 1 ,-1) NW ( 0 ,-1) W (-1 , 0) SW (-1 , 1) SE ( 0 , 1)

For every radius k (k ≥ 1) the ring k begins in the east at (k,0);  
it is traced clockwise along the directions

NW, W, SW, SE, E, NE  

each one repeated k times.  
Thus ring k contains 6k numbers and the last number of the ring is  

N(k)=1+3k(k+1).

-------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  Which ring contains 2026?
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Solve 2026 ≤ N(k):

N(25)=1+3·25·26=1951 < 2026  
N(26)=1+3·26·27=2107 ≥ 2026

Hence 2026 is on ring k = 26.  
The first number in that ring is therefore 1952.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
2.  Where on the ring is 2026?
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Offset inside the ring  
s = 2026 – 1952 = 74.  

Because every edge of ring 26 is 26 numbers long,

edge-index   = 74 // 26 = 2        (the 3rd edge)  
step on edge = 74 % 26  = 22.

Edge 2 is the SW edge whose vector is (-1, 1).  
Starting at (26,0) and moving

26 ×(0,-1) + 26 ×(-1,0) + 22 ×(-1,1)

gives the co-ordinates of 2026:

(26,0) → (26,-26) → (0,-26) → (-22,-4).

-------------------------------------------------------------------
3.  The six neighbouring co-ordinates
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Add the six step-vectors to (-22,-4):

1  (-21,-4)   (inner ring, k = 25)  
2  (-21,-5)   (same ring, k = 26)  
3  (-22,-5)   (outer ring, k = 27)  
4  (-23,-4)   (outer ring, k = 27)  
5  (-23,-3)   (same ring, k = 26)  
6  (-22,-3)   (inner ring, k = 25)

-------------------------------------------------------------------
4.  Convert these positions to their numbers
-------------------------------------------------------------------
A point on ring k with
   • edge e (0–5) and
   • step t (0–k) along that edge
has offset  o = e·k + t ,
so its number is 1952 + o for k = 26, or 1802 + o for k = 25, or
2108 + o for k = 27 (because 2108 = N(26)+1).

Doing this for the six neighbours gives

1  (-21,-4)  k=25, edge 2, t=21  → 1802+71 = 1873  
2  (-21,-5)  k=26, edge 2, t=21  → 1952+73 = 2025  
3  (-22,-5)  k=27, edge 2, t=22  → 2108+76 = 2184  
4  (-23,-4)  k=27, edge 2, t=23  → 2108+77 = 2185  
5  (-23,-3)  k=26, edge 2, t=23  → 1952+75 = 2027  
6  (-22,-3)  k=25, edge 2, t=22  → 1802+72 = 1874

-------------------------------------------------------------------
5.  Sum of the neighbours
-------------------------------------------------------------------
1873 + 2025 + 2184 + 2185 + 2027 + 1874 = 12 168.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Answer
The sum of the six numbers adjacent to 2026 is 12 168.
